        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 17 at 12:53PM EDT by NWS Albany NY</headline>
        <description>At 1252 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Duanesburg, or near Rotterdam, moving northeast at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Glenridge, Hoffmans, Harding Crossing, West Milton, Willow Glen,
Garrison Manor, Wayville, Princetown, Woodruff Heights, Elnora, Halls
Corner, Grays Corners, Mannings Cove, Hutchinson Crossing, Clifton
Park Center, North Milton, Mariaville Lake, Rexford, Altamont, and
Valley Falls.

People attending Niska Day 2025 should seek safe shelter immediately!

This includes the following highways...
Interstate 88 between exits 24 and 25.
Interstate 90 between exits 25 and 26.
Interstate 890 between exits 1a and 9.
Interstate 87 between exits 8A and 13N.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 800 PM EDT for
eastern and east central New York.</instruction>
